Get Storet ID

get_storet_id.Rd

Helps users obtain the appropriate storet ID for a given analyte

get_storet_id(analyte)

Arguments

analyte

common name of chemical

Examples

get_storet_id("c")

#> # A tibble: 218 x 2
#>    storet analyte                     
#>    <chr>  <chr>                       
#>  1 00081  COLOR                       
#>  2 00086  ODOR THRESHOLD @ 60 C       
#>  3 00095  SPECIFIC CONDUCTANCE        
#>  4 01032  CHROMIUM, HEXAVALENT        
#>  5 77288  DICHLOROACETIC ACID (DCAA)  
#>  6 82721  DIBROMOACETIC ACID (DBAA)   
#>  7 82723  TRICHLOROACETIC ACID (TCAA) 
#>  8 A-041  MONOBROMOACETIC ACID (MBAA) 
#>  9 A-042  MONOCHLOROACETIC ACID (MCAA)
#> 10 A-049  HALOACETIC ACIDS (5) (HAA5) 
#> # … with 208 more rows
get_storet_id("Color")

#> # A tibble: 1 x 2
#>   storet analyte
#>   <chr>  <chr>  
#> 1 00081  COLOR  
get_storet_id("COLOR")

#> # A tibble: 1 x 2
#>   storet analyte
#>   <chr>  <chr>  
#> 1 00081  COLOR
